title: Ecuador's Latest Free Trade Agreements Aim for Economic Growth - Bloomberg Tax
summary: Ecuador has forged trade agreements with several countries to boost its economy and encourage sustainable development by attracting foreign investors and technology transfer. These agreements involve the reduction or elimination of tariffs for imports and exports, impacting tax collection and presenting challenges and opportunities for Ecuadorian businesses.
likely_naics_codes: Likely NAICS Codes: 425120 - Wholesale Trade Agents and Brokers, 423610 - Electrical Apparatus and Equipment, Wiring Supplies, and Related Equipment Merchant Wholesalers, 541614 - Process, Physical Distribution, and Logistics Consulting Services, 334510 - Electromedical and Electrotherapeutic Apparatus Manufacturing
